The `docker.io/library` prefix is a hardwired default that we pick up from the image library when it's asked for the full version of a parsed image's name (an `ImageReference`), and there was no domain portion in the value that we originally parsed.  This should prevent that.

I'm still not sure about using the whole pathname as part of the image's name, but that's not something that this changes.

@rh-atomic-bot r+
